WEBVTT

00:02.248 --> 00:04.786
-(music playing)
-(rodents squeaking)

00:04.820 --> 00:07.091
(indistinct chatter)

00:07.124 --> 00:08.761
(horn honking)

00:12.067 --> 00:14.272
(laughter)

00:14.305 --> 00:16.276
WOMAN:
Thank you.

00:16.309 --> 00:18.346
-MAN: Thank you.
-WOMAN 2: Sorry.

00:23.691 --> 00:26.095
-(piano playing soft music)
-(indistinct chatter)

00:31.674 --> 00:33.711
(elevator bell dings)

00:39.455 --> 00:42.127
Oh. (laughs) Captain Ross.

00:42.161 --> 00:44.131
Hey, Tawny.

00:44.165 --> 00:46.236
Yeah, I was just having a quick
nightcap with the other girls.

00:46.269 --> 00:47.706
They were wondering
where you were.

00:47.739 --> 00:50.244
Oh, you know.
Off to get some ice.

00:50.277 --> 00:52.114
I am just bushed.

00:52.147 --> 00:54.218
Know how you feel.

00:54.252 --> 00:57.559
Since we're both staying in,
maybe we could stay together.

00:57.592 --> 01:00.531
-(elevator bell dings)
-That's, um...

01:00.565 --> 01:03.704
-a very nice offer, Tawny.
-Mm.

01:03.738 --> 01:07.111
I'm extremely flattered,
but I'm also...

01:07.144 --> 01:09.115
Oh.

01:09.148 --> 01:11.286
You know the funny thing
about these?

01:11.319 --> 01:13.758
They come right off.

01:14.760 --> 01:16.730
Sorry.

01:16.764 --> 01:18.601
Mine doesn't come off.

01:18.634 --> 01:20.705
Excuse me.

01:20.738 --> 01:22.842
("In the Heat of the Moment"
by Willy DeVille playing)

01:22.876 --> 01:24.646
(Tawny sighs)

01:25.615 --> 01:27.519
(siren wailing)

01:32.896 --> 01:35.167
♪ I walk in the sidewalk ♪

01:36.369 --> 01:38.473
♪ And I feel like ♪

01:39.810 --> 01:43.116
♪ Every part of me ♪

01:43.149 --> 01:46.389
♪ Mm, is watchin' you ♪

01:47.358 --> 01:49.696
♪ Just like some kind
of vision ♪

01:51.600 --> 01:54.405
♪ Comin' so close ♪

01:55.508 --> 01:57.378
♪ And like in a dream ♪

01:58.848 --> 02:01.152
♪ You're just out of reach ♪

02:02.321 --> 02:06.162
♪ Let my pistols click,
make my zip unzip ♪

02:06.195 --> 02:07.732
(lighter clicks off)

02:09.569 --> 02:11.907
♪ Make my racing heart flutter ♪

02:11.940 --> 02:13.878
♪ Let me have my fun ♪

02:15.247 --> 02:17.619
(distant groaning)

02:17.652 --> 02:19.523
♪ But in the heat
of the moment ♪

02:19.556 --> 02:22.428
♪ Don't you forget ♪

02:22.461 --> 02:25.334
♪ In the heat of the moment,
I'll be movin' in ♪

02:25.367 --> 02:27.338
♪ In the heat of the moment ♪

02:27.371 --> 02:29.843
♪ Don't you forget ♪

02:29.876 --> 02:32.849
♪ All the things
that we haven't done yet ♪

02:34.986 --> 02:37.391
♪ Oh. ♪

02:39.596 --> 02:42.201
(siren whoops)

02:42.234 --> 02:43.537
MAN:
Back up!

02:43.571 --> 02:45.407
(horn honks twice)

02:46.977 --> 02:48.881
(indistinct chatter)

02:48.914 --> 02:50.685
Hope you haven't
had breakfast yet.

02:50.718 --> 02:52.622
Yeah?

02:52.655 --> 02:54.258
Just did.

02:54.291 --> 02:56.462
Poor guy over there,
fishing with his son

02:56.497 --> 02:57.932
when he spotted the body.

02:57.966 --> 03:00.203
Fishing in the Hudson?
You're shitting me.

03:00.237 --> 03:02.274
(indistinct radio transmission)

03:05.648 --> 03:07.652
Oh, my God. Jesus.

03:07.685 --> 03:10.290
-ID?
-Just this.

03:10.323 --> 03:11.827
The Brownstone.

03:11.860 --> 03:13.931
-It's a fruit stand over on...
-Yeah, I know what it is.

03:13.964 --> 03:17.672
Anything else?
I don't see any visible wounds.

03:17.706 --> 03:19.710
Besides the obvious one.

03:19.743 --> 03:21.279
WOMAN:
Neck was severed around
the fourth cervical vertebra,

03:21.312 --> 03:23.283
right through the vocal cords.

03:23.316 --> 03:26.724
Well, at least we know what he
was doing right before he died.

03:26.757 --> 03:28.794
Yeah, Mulcahy?
What was he doing?

03:28.828 --> 03:30.263
Giving head.

03:30.297 --> 03:32.802
(laughter)

03:32.836 --> 03:34.506
HANNAH:
The levels of multiplication

03:34.539 --> 03:36.275
and mutation are more rapid
than anything

03:36.309 --> 03:38.413
-I've ever seen.
-Mm.

03:38.446 --> 03:40.417
And you're sure the samples
were properly handled?

03:40.450 --> 03:41.754
I went out to Fire Island

03:41.787 --> 03:43.456
and collected
and prepared them myself.

03:43.491 --> 03:46.262
WILLIAM:
And the symptoms
when they're displayed?

03:46.295 --> 03:48.534
Seizures, skin infection,

03:48.567 --> 03:50.437
liver failure.

03:51.874 --> 03:53.376
You have to get out there,

03:53.410 --> 03:55.480
talk to the mayor,
chief of police.

03:55.515 --> 03:58.988
At this level of mutation
and multiplication,

03:59.021 --> 04:01.927
we can have an epidemic
on our hands in months.

04:01.960 --> 04:03.798
MANNEY:
What happened to it?

04:03.831 --> 04:07.304
HANNAH:
It has a virus, a new one.

04:07.337 --> 04:08.874
I've been taking samples
from deer carcasses

04:08.908 --> 04:10.845
out on the island
for over a year,

04:10.878 --> 04:12.949
ever since the first buck died
with similar symptoms.

04:12.982 --> 04:15.621
MANNEY:
We've definitely been finding
more dead ones as of late.

04:15.655 --> 04:18.326
One of my deputies found three
dead together the other day.

04:18.359 --> 04:19.896
Looked like a family.

04:19.930 --> 04:22.334
Whatever this virus is,
it's highly communicable,

04:22.367 --> 04:24.338
and it could be mutating
too quickly

04:24.371 --> 04:26.543
for the deer's immune system
to fight it.

04:26.577 --> 04:29.014
LEMBEK:
If these deer here
are isolated on an island,

04:29.048 --> 04:32.555
then how the hell did they
suddenly catch some new disease?

04:32.589 --> 04:35.327
New diseases are born every day.
That's science.

04:35.360 --> 04:37.397
As scary as it may seem,

04:37.431 --> 04:39.068
if we don't start
mitigation efforts soon,

04:39.101 --> 04:41.707
it's going to wipe out
the entire population.

04:41.740 --> 04:44.311
You're going to have to kill
all the deer on this island.

04:44.345 --> 04:46.617
LEMBEK:
And if we don't,
they're all gonna die?

04:46.650 --> 04:49.589
HANNAH:
The deer are simply
the first carriers of the virus.

04:49.623 --> 04:52.361
And the way that it's mutating,
it could leap to humans

04:52.394 --> 04:53.831
if it hasn't already.

04:54.866 --> 04:56.469
Then we're gonna have to arm up

04:56.503 --> 04:58.674
and shoot down every deer
on this island.

05:01.112 --> 05:02.615
(rhythmic, mechanical beeping)

05:02.649 --> 05:04.686
(siren blaring)

05:19.649 --> 05:22.087
-What do you think?
-WOMAN: Hard to tell.

05:22.120 --> 05:24.458
Rats got to the head,
and the body was deformed

05:24.493 --> 05:26.095
-by the water.
-Right.

05:26.128 --> 05:28.534
Those cuts look pretty similar
to me.

05:28.567 --> 05:30.805
Could be, but I couldn't tell
you if they were the same blade.

05:30.838 --> 05:32.675
Well, come on. It's got to be.

05:32.709 --> 05:34.411
You know, if this was the head
and body of a pretty blonde

05:34.445 --> 05:36.683
16-year-old from Riverdale,
you'd have ten detectives

05:36.717 --> 05:39.088
-down here on the case.
-Hold up.

05:39.121 --> 05:42.662
Someone stuffed it
down in there pretty good.

05:42.695 --> 05:44.398
Holy shit.

05:44.431 --> 05:46.068
Was that the cause of death?

05:46.102 --> 05:47.906
Or could somebody have stuffed
that down there post-mortem?

05:47.939 --> 05:49.709
Teeth are intact, which means

05:49.743 --> 05:52.014
he probably didn't struggle
when it was being put in.

05:52.047 --> 05:55.922
Don't the homosexuals use
colored handkerchiefs like this

05:55.955 --> 05:57.825
to let others know
what they're into?

05:57.859 --> 06:00.932
Saw something about it
on Donahue.

06:01.900 --> 06:03.771
Thanks.

06:04.773 --> 06:06.543
(indistinct chatter)

06:06.577 --> 06:09.014
Where's Gino Barelli?

06:10.685 --> 06:13.389
We want to lodge
a formal complaint.

06:13.423 --> 06:15.393
What do I look like,
your hairdresser?

06:15.427 --> 06:17.565
Ha! Your paper is here
to serve the gay community,

06:17.599 --> 06:19.101
but you're ignoring half of it.

06:19.134 --> 06:21.405
Listen, if you want
to apply for a job

06:21.439 --> 06:23.611
or submit a freelance article

06:23.644 --> 06:25.982
or an op-ed,
please, be my guest.

06:26.015 --> 06:27.785
Hey, lesbians have issues, too.

06:27.819 --> 06:29.856
Why don't you ever write
about women's health issues?

06:29.889 --> 06:32.060
How the ERA is
completely stalled out?

06:32.094 --> 06:33.998
How we can't get access
to health care...

06:34.031 --> 06:35.868
Yeah. Write about that.

06:35.902 --> 06:38.106
You know, I would really love
to write about those issues,

06:38.139 --> 06:41.078
but I'm a gay man,
so I write about issues

06:41.112 --> 06:42.916
that are important to gay men.

06:42.949 --> 06:45.053
Oh, yeah? What are you writing
about that's so important?

06:46.990 --> 06:48.961
I'm writing about how gay men
are being hunted

06:48.994 --> 06:50.598
and killed in this town.

06:50.631 --> 06:52.034
Wasn't us.

06:52.067 --> 06:54.673
All right, ladies,
it's time to go.

06:57.210 --> 07:00.651
-Wait. This is a...
Is this a threat?
-FRAN: No.

07:00.685 --> 07:02.822
Sounds like you need something
to protect yourself.

07:13.109 --> 07:14.713
(door opens)

07:14.746 --> 07:16.482
Is that you?

07:18.921 --> 07:20.558
Something smells good.

07:20.591 --> 07:22.829
PATRICK:
Oh. Beef Bolognese.

07:29.542 --> 07:30.911
How was your day?

07:30.945 --> 07:32.882
GINO (sighing):
Oh...

07:35.821 --> 07:38.560
Really? I didn't know
our mayor liked boys.

07:38.594 --> 07:41.633
(laughs)
Homophobic Hall of Shame.

07:41.667 --> 07:43.971
First annual issue.

07:44.004 --> 07:46.777
You should thank me
for not including you.

07:46.810 --> 07:48.781
-Funny.
-Seriously.

07:48.814 --> 07:51.118
Your precinct has more
complaints from the community

07:51.152 --> 07:52.889
than any other precinct
in Manhattan.

07:52.922 --> 07:55.126
It's just a lot of old-school
guys all in one place.

07:55.160 --> 07:56.963
Keep defending them.

07:56.997 --> 07:59.736
You should quit
and do something else.

07:59.769 --> 08:01.807
I don't know how
to do anything else.

08:02.809 --> 08:04.813
That's not exactly true.

08:04.846 --> 08:06.883
(Patrick chuckles)

08:12.895 --> 08:14.766
What's the matter?
You look tense.

08:14.799 --> 08:17.104
We found another body.

08:18.072 --> 08:20.611
By the piers.
He was missing a head.

08:20.644 --> 08:22.915
What the fuck?

08:24.652 --> 08:26.523
Oh, Jesus, Patrick.

08:26.556 --> 08:28.727
-That's three now.
-Mm-hmm.

08:28.761 --> 08:30.698
Is the department gonna hold
a press conference?

08:30.731 --> 08:32.100
-People need to know about this.
-No.

08:32.134 --> 08:33.804
And I am telling you this
off the record.

08:33.837 --> 08:36.810
I'm not supposed to talk
about this with anyone.

08:36.843 --> 08:38.814
I'm not "anyone."

08:38.847 --> 08:40.818
I'm the guy
you supposedly love.

08:40.851 --> 08:42.755
I should be writing about--

08:42.789 --> 08:45.761
Hell, the New York Times
should be writing about it,

08:45.795 --> 08:47.865
-and you should be helping.
-I-I can't.

08:47.899 --> 08:49.301
Gino, we have talked about this.

08:49.334 --> 08:50.971
We have to keep
our professional lives separate.

08:51.005 --> 08:53.042
Oh, really?
When it's life-and-death?

08:53.076 --> 08:55.146
-Those are the rules?
-Just think
what you want to think.

08:55.180 --> 08:59.088
But I am not going to jeopardize
my career to be your source.

08:59.121 --> 09:01.760
The fuck good are you?

09:01.793 --> 09:03.096
(Gino sighs)

09:03.129 --> 09:06.001
What the fuck am I doing?

09:06.035 --> 09:08.841
-What am I doing?
-What are you talking about?

09:08.874 --> 09:11.980
What the fuck
am I doing with you?

09:12.013 --> 09:15.153
Here in this sham
of a relationship?

09:15.186 --> 09:16.623
Hey, hey, hey, no.
Don't say that.

09:16.656 --> 09:18.092
It's not a sham, okay?

09:18.126 --> 09:19.696
I did not go through
everything

09:19.729 --> 09:21.031
that I've gone through
in my life

09:21.065 --> 09:23.069
to go back into the closet
for a guy

09:23.102 --> 09:25.841
who does not want
to be what he truly is.

09:25.875 --> 09:30.083
Yeah, maybe, but I am
very good in bed.

09:32.320 --> 09:33.757
(soft chuckle)

09:37.932 --> 09:40.270
(sighs)

09:43.176 --> 09:45.280
Gino...

09:48.085 --> 09:50.190
I am doing the best I can.

09:54.298 --> 09:55.801
Maybe that's just...

09:55.835 --> 09:58.607
That's not enough.

09:58.640 --> 10:00.611
We need you.

10:00.644 --> 10:02.147
I need you.

10:07.925 --> 10:09.963
Not like this.

10:11.031 --> 10:13.002
Where are you going?

10:13.035 --> 10:15.140
Somewhere.

10:15.173 --> 10:17.845
-Anywhere where I'm not hiding.
-Mm.

10:17.879 --> 10:20.083
Or helping someone to hide.

10:21.252 --> 10:24.324
Come on, Gino. Let's just...

10:24.358 --> 10:25.861
(door opens)

10:25.895 --> 10:27.632
(door closes)

10:29.034 --> 10:31.238
(sighs)
Shit.

10:34.813 --> 10:36.750
SHERIFF (on TV):
Mr. Ewing?

10:36.783 --> 10:38.921
-Yeah.
-Mr. Barnes made
a very serious accusation.

10:38.954 --> 10:40.658
He claims you pushed
Miss Shepard off that balcony.

10:40.691 --> 10:42.060
J.R.:
That man is a damn liar.

10:42.093 --> 10:43.897
I saw him...

10:43.931 --> 10:45.400
ADAM:
I was watching that.

10:45.433 --> 10:47.137
Mm. Come on.
Get yourself cleaned up.

10:47.170 --> 10:49.074
You're coming out with me.

10:49.107 --> 10:51.212
I don't want to go anywhere.

10:52.247 --> 10:54.318
Fuck off, Sully.

10:54.351 --> 10:56.322
You have been eating
breakfast cereal and watching TV

10:56.355 --> 10:58.226
for six days.

10:58.259 --> 11:02.000
Adam, I could understand one day
'cause of his hot little accent,

11:02.033 --> 11:05.173
but any longer is just
you feeling sorry for yourself.

11:05.206 --> 11:07.712
I was falling in love with him.

11:07.745 --> 11:10.049
Bullshit. You were falling
in love with falling in love.

11:10.083 --> 11:12.120
Get off of me.

11:13.322 --> 11:15.293
I really need you tonight.

11:15.326 --> 11:16.830
I got to do some business,

11:16.863 --> 11:18.232
and I don't want
to go out there alone.

11:18.266 --> 11:20.370
Are those drugs?

11:20.403 --> 11:22.040
What's the hurry
with selling ludes?

11:22.073 --> 11:24.077
The price is skyrocketing,
I really need the money,

11:24.111 --> 11:25.948
and you really need
some fresh air.

11:26.950 --> 11:28.720
Fine.

11:28.754 --> 11:31.826
Where are we going?
What is this?

11:31.860 --> 11:34.097
Only one of the best places
in the world.

11:34.131 --> 11:36.335
(indistinct shouting)

11:36.368 --> 11:38.339
You're not here
to sell those pills, are you?

11:38.372 --> 11:40.210
Okay, so maybe I lied.

11:40.243 --> 11:42.414
Had to get you
off that couch, okay?

11:42.447 --> 11:44.384
-This is dirty.
-I'm doing you a favor.

11:44.418 --> 11:46.255
It's giving me the creeps.

11:46.288 --> 11:49.228
Well, I'm shaking, but it's not
'cause they're creeps.

11:50.230 --> 11:52.100
(indistinct chatter)

11:56.175 --> 11:57.845
Tell me you're not going
anywhere with that guy.

11:57.878 --> 11:59.916
Be cool. Groove with it.

12:00.951 --> 12:02.922
-Hey.
-Hey.

12:06.295 --> 12:09.167
-What am I supposed to do?
-Have fun.

12:24.832 --> 12:26.870
(sighs)

12:30.043 --> 12:31.412
Sully?

12:34.418 --> 12:36.455
Sully?!

12:37.925 --> 12:39.294
Come on, Sully.

12:39.328 --> 12:42.133
(rustling in brush)

12:48.045 --> 12:51.886
Hey, man,
I-I don't want any trouble.

12:58.165 --> 12:59.368
Sully?!

12:59.401 --> 13:03.275
Adam? Sorry.
That's my roommate.

13:03.309 --> 13:06.081
-Adam?
-Sully?

13:07.083 --> 13:08.987
Adam?

13:10.089 --> 13:12.160
(grunts)

13:13.262 --> 13:15.400
Adam?

13:18.840 --> 13:21.412
Great. Just great.

13:28.326 --> 13:30.898
-(yelling)
-Sully?

13:31.933 --> 13:34.037
(panting)

13:37.110 --> 13:38.479
Okay, tell me again.

13:38.513 --> 13:41.385
How was this tall individual
dressed?

13:41.418 --> 13:45.326
He was wearing a-a hood
and all leather,

13:45.360 --> 13:47.565
and, uh, he wasn't just tall.

13:47.598 --> 13:49.267
-He was gigantic.
-PATRICK: Okay.

13:49.301 --> 13:52.173
Okay, but, uh, his dress--

13:52.207 --> 13:54.311
by leather clothes, would
you say he was a leather man?

13:55.446 --> 13:58.486
Part of a gay, uh,
leather subculture?

13:58.520 --> 14:02.495
Like what you might find
at places like, uh, uh,

14:02.528 --> 14:04.431
The Backfill Club?

14:04.464 --> 14:07.303
I don't know.
I-I have... never been.

14:07.337 --> 14:09.274
I haven't been anywhere
like that.

14:10.276 --> 14:11.579
(typing)

14:11.613 --> 14:13.517
(indistinct chatter)

14:13.550 --> 14:16.155
You're gonna tell me you can't
do anything, aren't you?

14:17.190 --> 14:19.161
I knew this was a waste of time.

14:20.363 --> 14:22.100
You don't give a shit about us.

14:22.133 --> 14:24.071
Every day, we're getting beaten,
and we are dying,

14:24.104 --> 14:27.210
-and the police
don't give a shit.
-Cut the drama, okay?

14:27.243 --> 14:29.247
If that were true,
I would not have had

14:29.281 --> 14:31.218
to chuck my shoes away
because they were covered

14:31.251 --> 14:33.055
in polluted river water.

14:41.004 --> 14:43.242
So there was a body
by the piers?

14:43.275 --> 14:44.912
And you're looking into it.

14:44.946 --> 14:46.616
Oh, I just bring it out
to make a point, okay?

14:46.649 --> 14:49.121
Some of us actually care.

14:49.154 --> 14:50.958
And the reason
I can't help you today is not

14:50.991 --> 14:52.293
because
your roommate's homosexual.

14:52.327 --> 14:53.630
It's because
he's only been missing 12 hours.

14:53.663 --> 14:55.601
Plus, there is no evidence
of a crime.

14:55.634 --> 14:58.372
What about that scream
in the park? That guy?

14:58.406 --> 15:01.145
You heard a yell, and
some leather guy followed you.

15:01.178 --> 15:03.950
Go home.
Wait for your roommate.

15:03.984 --> 15:05.286
If he doesn't show up
by Thursday,

15:05.319 --> 15:06.623
you come back and see me.

15:06.656 --> 15:08.192
I'll take a full report.

15:15.974 --> 15:17.678
MARZARA:
You just sent the guy away
'cause it's not

15:17.711 --> 15:19.715
a missing persons case.
What are we talking about?

15:19.749 --> 15:21.418
Maybe we should look into it.

15:21.452 --> 15:24.057
The body in the river,
the two others last month?

15:24.090 --> 15:25.594
I'm getting a very bad feeling
in my gut.

15:25.627 --> 15:26.629
Yeah, I get a bad feeling
in my gut

15:26.663 --> 15:28.232
every time I open the newspaper.

15:28.265 --> 15:29.669
I'm worried we're seeing
a pattern here, Chief.

15:29.702 --> 15:31.973
Someone could be targeting
the gay community.

15:32.006 --> 15:33.543
Five people dead

15:33.577 --> 15:35.948
is a Friday night in the Bronx,
it's not a pattern.

15:35.981 --> 15:37.484
Let me tell you something.

15:37.518 --> 15:40.256
The people that make up
that "community"?

